Re: 0.3.1 release candidate, please test

Bitcointalk

2010-07-16 17:26:17 UTC - [11]Original Post

   Good point.  If youʼre going to have more than 8 LAN nodes connect to
   one gateway node, then youʼd better have the gateway node set up so it
   can receive incoming connections.  Otherwise, while the gateway node
   has 8 or more connections, it will not try to add any more outbound
   connections.  As the outside nodes youʼre connected to come and go, it
   doesnʼt make new outbound connections to replace them.  Youʼll be fine
   if you can accept incoming connections, then there will be plenty of
   others connecting to you.
